    {
      "id": "line-57",
      "sectionId": "passage-1",
      "sectionTitle": "PASSAGE 1",
      "speaker": "",
      "text": "A new study has found that regular exercise can improve brain function and reduce the risk of cognitive decline in older adults.",
      "type": "narration",
      "words": 22,
      "start": 562.74,
      "end": 572.24,
      "matchedWords": 4
    },
    {
      "id": "line-58",
      "sectionId": "passage-1",
      "sectionTitle": "PASSAGE 1",
      "speaker": "",
      "text": "The study, which was conducted by researchers at the University of California, followed 1,000 adults over the age of 65 for five years.",
      "type": "narration",
      "words": 24,
      "start": 572.24,
      "end": 728.874,
      "matchedWords": 11
    },
    {
      "id": "line-59",
      "sectionId": "passage-1",
      "sectionTitle": "PASSAGE 1",
      "speaker": "",
      "text": "The participants were divided into two groups.",
      "type": "narration",
      "words": 7,
      "start": 728.874,
      "end": 774.559,
      "matchedWords": 0
    },
    {
      "id": "line-60",
      "sectionId": "passage-1",
      "sectionTitle": "PASSAGE 1",
      "speaker": "",
      "text": "One group engaged in moderate exercise, such as walking or swimming, for at least 30 minutes a day, three days a week.",
      "type": "narration",
      "words": 22,
      "start": 774.559,
      "end": 918.14,
      "matchedWords": 0
    },
    {
      "id": "line-61",
      "sectionId": "passage-1",
      "sectionTitle": "PASSAGE 1",
      "speaker": "",
      "text": "The other group did not engage in any regular exercise.",
      "type": "narration",
      "words": 10,
      "start": 918.14,
      "end": 1098.74,
      "matchedWords": 4
    },
    {
      "id": "line-62",
      "sectionId": "passage-1",
      "sectionTitle": "PASSAGE 1",
      "speaker": "",
      "text": "At the end of the five-year period, the researchers found that the exercise group had better memory, attention, and problem-solving skills than the non-exercise group.",
      "type": "narration",
      "words": 28,
      "start": 1098.74,
      "end": 1164.759,
      "matchedWords": 8
    },
    {
      "id": "line-63",
      "sectionId": "passage-1",
      "sectionTitle": "PASSAGE 1",
      "speaker": "",
      "text": "They also had a lower risk of developing dementia.",
      "type": "narration",
      "words": 9,
      "start": 1164.759,
      "end": 1185.98,
      "matchedWords": 0
    },
    {
      "id": "line-64",
      "sectionId": "passage-1",
      "sectionTitle": "PASSAGE 1",
      "speaker": "",
      "text": "The researchers explain that exercise increases blood flow to the brain, which helps to nourish brain cells and promote the growth of new neurons.",
      "type": "narration",
      "words": 24,
      "start": 1185.98,
      "end": 1297.264,
      "matchedWords": 7
    },
    {
      "id": "line-65",
      "sectionId": "passage-1",
      "sectionTitle": "PASSAGE 1",
      "speaker": "",
      "text": "It also reduces inflammation and oxidative stress, which are both associated with cognitive decline.",
      "type": "narration",
      "words": 14,
      "start": 1297.264,
      "end": 1362.18,
      "matchedWords": 0
    },
    {
      "id": "line-66",
      "sectionId": "passage-1",
      "sectionTitle": "PASSAGE 1",
      "speaker": "",
      "text": "The study suggests that regular exercise is a simple and effective way to maintain brain health as we age.",
      "type": "narration",
      "words": 19,
      "start": 1362.18,
      "end": 1383.25,
      "matchedWords": 4
    },
    {
      "id": "line-67",
      "sectionId": "passage-1",
      "sectionTitle": "PASSAGE 1",
      "speaker": "",
      "text": "Even moderate exercise, such as walking, can have significant benefits.",
      "type": "narration",
      "words": 10,
      "start": 1383.25,
      "end": 1394.34,
      "matchedWords": 0
    },
    {
      "id": "line-68",
      "sectionId": "passage-1",
      "sectionTitle": "PASSAGE 1",
      "speaker": "Q9.",
      "text": "What did the researchers at the University of California find?",
      "type": "question",
      "words": 10,
