    },
    {
      "id": "line-70",
      "sectionId": "passage-1",
      "sectionTitle": "PASSAGE 1",
      "speaker": "Q11.",
      "text": "Why does exercise improve brain function?",
      "type": "question",
      "words": 6,
      "start": 1397.298,
      "end": 1398.603,
      "matchedWords": 0
    },
    {
      "id": "line-71",
      "sectionId": "passage-2",
      "sectionTitle": "PASSAGE 2",
      "speaker": "",
      "text": "The Internet of Things (IoT) is a network of physical devices, vehicles, home appliances, and other items embedded with electronics, software, sensors, and connectivity, which enables these objects to connect and exchange data.",
      "type": "narration",
      "words": 33,
      "start": 1398.603,
      "end": 1401.474,
      "matchedWords": 0
    },
    {
      "id": "line-72",
      "sectionId": "passage-2",
      "sectionTitle": "PASSAGE 2",
      "speaker": "",
      "text": "The IoT has the potential to transform many aspects of our lives.",
      "type": "narration",
      "words": 12,
      "start": 1401.474,
      "end": 1402.518,
      "matchedWords": 0
    },
    {
      "id": "line-73",
      "sectionId": "passage-2",
      "sectionTitle": "PASSAGE 2",
      "speaker": "",
      "text": "For example, smart homes can automatically adjust the temperature, turn on the lights, and lock the doors based on our preferences.",
      "type": "narration",
      "words": 21,
      "start": 1402.518,
      "end": 1404.345,
      "matchedWords": 0
    },
    {
      "id": "line-74",
      "sectionId": "passage-2",
      "sectionTitle": "PASSAGE 2",
      "speaker": "",
      "text": "Smart cars can communicate with each other and with traffic lights to reduce accidents and improve traffic flow.",
      "type": "narration",
      "words": 18,
      "start": 1404.345,
      "end": 1405.911,
      "matchedWords": 0
    },
    {
      "id": "line-75",
      "sectionId": "passage-2",
      "sectionTitle": "PASSAGE 2",
      "speaker": "",
      "text": "However, the IoT also raises some concerns.",
      "type": "narration",
      "words": 7,
      "start": 1405.911,
      "end": 1406.52,
      "matchedWords": 0
    },
    {
      "id": "line-76",
      "sectionId": "passage-2",
      "sectionTitle": "PASSAGE 2",
      "speaker": "",
      "text": "One of the main concerns is security.",
      "type": "narration",
      "words": 7,
      "start": 1406.52,
      "end": 1436.88,
      "matchedWords": 3
    },
    {
      "id": "line-77",
      "sectionId": "passage-2",
      "sectionTitle": "PASSAGE 2",
      "speaker": "",
      "text": "As more devices become connected to the Internet, they become vulnerable to hacking and cyberattacks.",
      "type": "narration",
      "words": 15,
      "start": 1436.88,
      "end": 1442.376,
      "matchedWords": 6
    },
    {
      "id": "line-78",
      "sectionId": "passage-2",
      "sectionTitle": "PASSAGE 2",
      "speaker": "",
      "text": "Hackers could potentially gain access to our personal information, control our devices, or even cause physical harm.",
      "type": "narration",
      "words": 17,
      "start": 1442.376,
      "end": 1448.605,
      "matchedWords": 0
    },
    {
      "id": "line-79",
      "sectionId": "passage-2",
      "sectionTitle": "PASSAGE 2",
      "speaker": "",
      "text": "Another concern is privacy.",
      "type": "narration",
      "words": 4,
      "start": 1448.605,
      "end": 1450.07,
      "matchedWords": 0
    },
    {
      "id": "line-80",
      "sectionId": "passage-2",
      "sectionTitle": "PASSAGE 2",
      "speaker": "",
      "text": "The IoT generates a huge amount of data about our daily lives.",
      "type": "narration",
      "words": 12,
      "start": 1450.07,
      "end": 1454.467,
      "matchedWords": 0
    },
    {
      "id": "line-81",
      "sectionId": "passage-2",
      "sectionTitle": "PASSAGE 2",
      "speaker": "",
      "text": "This data could be used by companies to target us with advertising, or by governments to monitor our activities.",
      "type": "narration",
      "words": 19,
      "start": 1454.467,
      "end": 1461.428,
      "matchedWords": 0
    },
    {
      "id": "line-82",
      "sectionId": "passage-2",
      "sectionTitle": "PASSAGE 2",
      "speaker": "",
      "text": "To address these concerns, we need to develop better security measures and privacy laws to protect users.",
      "type": "narration",
      "words": 17,
      "start": 1461.428,
      "end": 1467.657,
      "matchedWords": 0
    },
    {
      "id": "line-83",
      "sectionId": "passage-2",
      "sectionTitle": "PASSAGE 2",
      "speaker": "",
      "text": "We also need to educate people about the risks of the IoT and how to protect themselves.",
      "type": "narration",
      "words": 17,
      "start": 1467.657,
      "end": 1473.886,
      "matchedWords": 0
    },
    {
      "id": "line-84",
      "sectionId": "passage-2",
      "sectionTitle": "PASSAGE 2",
      "speaker": "Q12.",
      "text": "What is the Internet of Things?",
      "type": "question",
      "words": 6,
      "start": 1473.886,
      "end": 1479.382,
      "matchedWords": 0
    },
    {
      "id": "line-85",
      "sectionId": "passage-2",
      "sectionTitle": "PASSAGE 2",
      "speaker": "Q13.",
      "text": "What is one of the potential benefits of the IoT?",
      "type": "question",
      "words": 10,
      "start": 1479.382,
      "end": 1486.343,
      "matchedWords": 0
    },
    {
      "id": "line-86",
      "sectionId": "passage-2",
      "sectionTitle": "PASSAGE 2",
      "speaker": "Q14.",
      "text": "What is one of the main concerns about the IoT?",
      "type": "question",
      "words": 10,
      "start": 1486.343,
      "end": 1493.305,
      "matchedWords": 0
    },
    {
      "id": "line-87",
      "sectionId": "passage-2",
      "sectionTitle": "PASSAGE 2",
      "speaker": "Q15.",
      "text": "What do we need to do to address the concerns about the IoT?",
      "type": "question",
      "words": 13,
      "start": 1493.305,
      "end": 1501.365,
      "matchedWords": 0
    },
    {
      "id": "line-88",
      "sectionId": "recording-1",
      "sectionTitle": "RECORDING 1",
      "speaker": "",
      "text": "Climate change is one of the most pressing issues facing the world today.",
      "type": "narration",
      "words": 13,
      "start": 1501.365,
      "end": 1506.129,
      "matchedWords": 0
    },
    {
      "id": "line-89",
      "sectionId": "recording-1",
      "sectionTitle": "RECORDING 1",
      "speaker": "",
      "text": "It is caused by the release of greenhouse gases, such as carbon dioxide, into the atmosphere.",
      "type": "narration",
      "words": 16,
      "start": 1506.129,
      "end": 1511.991,
      "matchedWords": 0
    },
    {
      "id": "line-90",
      "sectionId": "recording-1",
      "sectionTitle": "RECORDING 1",
      "speaker": "",
      "text": "These gases trap heat from the sun, causing the Earth's temperature to rise.",
      "type": "narration",
      "words": 13,
      "start": 1511.991,
      "end": 1516.754,
      "matchedWords": 0
    },
    {
      "id": "line-91",
      "sectionId": "recording-1",
      "sectionTitle": "RECORDING 1",
      "speaker": "",
      "text": "The effects of climate change are already being felt around the world.",
      "type": "narration",
      "words": 12,
      "start": 1516.754,
      "end": 1521.151,
      "matchedWords": 0
    },
    {
      "id": "line-92",
      "sectionId": "recording-1",
      "sectionTitle": "RECORDING 1",
      "speaker": "",
      "text": "We are seeing more frequent and severe heatwaves, droughts, floods, and storms.",
      "type": "narration",
      "words": 12,
      "start": 1521.151,
      "end": 1525.547,
      "matchedWords": 0
    },
    {
      "id": "line-93",
      "sectionId": "recording-1",
      "sectionTitle": "RECORDING 1",
      "speaker": "",
      "text": "These extreme weather events can cause significant damage to property, infrastructure, and agriculture, and can also lead to loss of life.",
      "type": "narration",
      "words": 21,
      "start": 1525.547,
      "end": 1533.242,
      "matchedWords": 0
    },
    {
      "id": "line-94",
      "sectionId": "recording-1",
      "sectionTitle": "RECORDING 1",
      "speaker": "",
      "text": "Climate change also has a negative impact on human health.",
      "type": "narration",
      "words": 10,
      "start": 1533.242,
      "end": 1536.906,
      "matchedWords": 0
    },
    {
      "id": "line-95",
      "sectionId": "recording-1",
      "sectionTitle": "RECORDING 1",
      "speaker": "",
      "text": "It can increase the spread of infectious diseases, such as malaria and dengue fever, as mosquitoes and other disease-carrying insects expand their range.",
      "type": "narration",
      "words": 24,
      "start": 1536.906,
      "end": 1545.699,
      "matchedWords": 0
    },
    {
      "id": "line-96",
      "sectionId": "recording-1",
      "sectionTitle": "RECORDING 1",
      "speaker": "",
      "text": "It can also cause respiratory problems due to air pollution and wildfires.",
      "type": "narration",
      "words": 12,
      "start": 1545.699,
      "end": 1550.096,
      "matchedWords": 0
    },
    {
      "id": "line-97",
      "sectionId": "recording-1",
      "sectionTitle": "RECORDING 1",
      "speaker": "",
      "text": "To address climate change, we need to reduce our greenhouse gas emissions.",
      "type": "narration",
      "words": 12,
      "start": 1550.096,
      "end": 1554.493,
      "matchedWords": 0
    },
    {
      "id": "line-98",
      "sectionId": "recording-1",
      "sectionTitle": "RECORDING 1",
      "speaker": "",
      "text": "This includes transitioning to renewable energy sources, such as solar and wind power, improving energy efficiency, and reducing our reliance on fossil fuels.",
      "type": "narration",
      "words": 23,
      "start": 1554.493,
      "end": 1562.92,
      "matchedWords": 0
    },
    {
      "id": "line-99",
      "sectionId": "recording-1",
      "sectionTitle": "RECORDING 1",
      "speaker": "",
      "text": "We also need to adapt to the changes that are already happening, such as building sea walls to protect against rising sea levels and developing drought-resistant crops.",
      "type": "narration",
      "words": 28,
      "start": 1562.92,
      "end": 1573.179,
      "matchedWords": 0
    },
    {
      "id": "line-100",
      "sectionId": "recording-1",
      "sectionTitle": "RECORDING 1",
      "speaker": "",
      "text": "In addition, we need to raise awareness about climate change and encourage people to take action.",
      "type": "narration",
      "words": 16,
      "start": 1573.179,
      "end": 1579.041,
      "matchedWords": 0
    },
    {
      "id": "line-101",
      "sectionId": "recording-1",
      "sectionTitle": "RECORDING 1",
      "speaker": "",
      "text": "Everyone can do their part by reducing their carbon footprint, such as driving less, using energy-efficient appliances, and eating less meat.",
      "type": "narration",
      "words": 22,
      "start": 1579.041,
      "end": 1587.102,
      "matchedWords": 0
    },
    {
      "id": "line-102",
      "sectionId": "recording-1",
      "sectionTitle": "RECORDING 1",
      "speaker": "Q16.",
      "text": "What causes climate change?",
      "type": "question",
      "words": 4,
      "start": 1587.102,
      "end": 1591.865,
      "matchedWords": 0
    },
    {
      "id": "line-103",
      "sectionId": "recording-1",
      "sectionTitle": "RECORDING 1",
      "speaker": "Q17.",
      "text": "What are some of the effects of climate change?",
      "type": "question",
      "words": 9,
      "start": 1591.865,
      "end": 1598.46,
      "matchedWords": 0
    },
    {
      "id": "line-104",
      "sectionId": "recording-1",
      "sectionTitle": "RECORDING 1",
      "speaker": "Q18.",
      "text": "What can we do to reduce greenhouse gas emissions?",
      "type": "question",
      "words": 9,
      "start": 1598.46,
      "end": 1599.19,
      "matchedWords": 3
    },
    {
      "id": "line-105",
      "sectionId": "recording-2",
      "sectionTitle": "RECORDING 2",
      "speaker": "",
      "text": "Artificial intelligence (AI) is rapidly changing the way we live and work.",
      "type": "narration",
      "words": 12,
      "start": 1599.19,
      "end": 1599.676,
      "matchedWords": 0
    },
    {
      "id": "line-106",
      "sectionId": "recording-2",
      "sectionTitle": "RECORDING 2",
      "speaker": "",
      "text": "It is being used in a wide range of industries, from healthcare and finance to transportation and education.",
      "type": "narration",
      "words": 18,
      "start": 1599.676,
      "end": 1600.406,
      "matchedWords": 0
    },
    {
      "id": "line-107",
      "sectionId": "recording-2",
      "sectionTitle": "RECORDING 2",
      "speaker": "",
      "text": "In healthcare, AI is being used to diagnose diseases, develop new drugs, and personalize treatment plans.",
      "type": "narration",
      "words": 16,
      "start": 1600.406,
      "end": 1601.055,
      "matchedWords": 0
    },
    {
      "id": "line-108",
      "sectionId": "recording-2",
      "sectionTitle": "RECORDING 2",
      "speaker": "",
      "text": "For example, AI algorithms can analyze medical images, such as X-rays and MRIs, to detect cancer and other diseases at an early stage.",
      "type": "narration",
      "words": 24,
      "start": 1601.055,
      "end": 1602.028,
      "matchedWords": 0
    },
    {
      "id": "line-109",
      "sectionId": "recording-2",
      "sectionTitle": "RECORDING 2",
      "speaker": "",
      "text": "In finance, AI is being used to detect fraud, manage risk, and provide financial advice.",
      "type": "narration",
      "words": 15,
      "start": 1602.028,
      "end": 1602.636,
      "matchedWords": 0
    },
    {
      "id": "line-110",
      "sectionId": "recording-2",
      "sectionTitle": "RECORDING 2",
      "speaker": "",
      "text": "AI algorithms can analyze large amounts of financial data to identify patterns and trends that humans might miss.",
      "type": "narration",
      "words": 18,
      "start": 1602.636,
      "end": 1603.366,
      "matchedWords": 0
    },
    {
      "id": "line-111",
      "sectionId": "recording-2",
      "sectionTitle": "RECORDING 2",
      "speaker": "",
      "text": "In transportation, AI is being used to develop self-driving cars and trucks.",
      "type": "narration",
      "words": 13,
      "start": 1603.366,
      "end": 1603.893,
      "matchedWords": 0
    },
    {
      "id": "line-112",
      "sectionId": "recording-2",
      "sectionTitle": "RECORDING 2",
      "speaker": "",
      "text": "Self-driving vehicles have the potential to reduce accidents, improve traffic flow, and make transportation more efficient.",
      "type": "narration",
      "words": 17,
      "start": 1603.893,
      "end": 1604.582,
      "matchedWords": 0
    },
    {
      "id": "line-113",
      "sectionId": "recording-2",
      "sectionTitle": "RECORDING 2",
      "speaker": "",
      "text": "However, AI also raises some ethical and social issues.",
      "type": "narration",
      "words": 9,
      "start": 1604.582,
      "end": 1604.947,
      "matchedWords": 0
    },
    {
      "id": "line-114",
      "sectionId": "recording-2",
      "sectionTitle": "RECORDING 2",
      "speaker": "",
      "text": "For example, there are concerns about job displacement, as AI systems can perform many tasks that are currently done by humans.",
      "type": "narration",
      "words": 21,
      "start": 1604.947,
      "end": 1605.799,
      "matchedWords": 0
    },
    {
      "id": "line-115",
      "sectionId": "recording-2",
      "sectionTitle": "RECORDING 2",
      "speaker": "",
      "text": "There are also concerns about bias in AI algorithms, which can lead to unfair treatment of certain groups of people.",
      "type": "narration",
      "words": 20,
      "start": 1605.799,
      "end": 1606.609,
      "matchedWords": 0
    },
    {
      "id": "line-116",
      "sectionId": "recording-2",
      "sectionTitle": "RECORDING 2",
      "speaker": "",
      "text": "To ensure that AI is used for the benefit of humanity, we need to develop ethical guidelines and regulations for its use.",
      "type": "narration",
      "words": 22,
      "start": 1606.609,
      "end": 1607.501,
      "matchedWords": 0
    },
    {
      "id": "line-117",
      "sectionId": "recording-2",
      "sectionTitle": "RECORDING 2",
      "speaker": "",
      "text": "We also need to invest in education and training to help people adapt to the changing job market.",
      "type": "narration",
      "words": 18,
      "start": 1607.501,
      "end": 1608.231,
      "matchedWords": 0
    },
    {
      "id": "line-118",
      "sectionId": "recording-2",
      "sectionTitle": "RECORDING 2",
      "speaker": "Q19.",
      "text": "What is AI being used for in healthcare?",
      "type": "question",
      "words": 8,
      "start": 1608.231,
      "end": 1608.92,
      "matchedWords": 0
    },
    {
      "id": "line-119",
      "sectionId": "recording-2",
      "sectionTitle": "RECORDING 2",
      "speaker": "Q20.",
      "text": "What is one of the potential benefits of self-driving vehicles?",
      "type": "question",
      "words": 11,
      "start": 1608.92,
      "end": 1609.731,
      "matchedWords": 0
    },
    {
      "id": "line-120",
      "sectionId": "recording-2",
      "sectionTitle": "RECORDING 2",
      "speaker": "Q21.",
      "text": "What are some of the ethical and social issues raised by AI?",
      "type": "question",
      "words": 12,
      "start": 1609.731,
      "end": 1610.583,
      "matchedWords": 0
    },
    {
      "id": "line-121",
      "sectionId": "recording-3",
      "sectionTitle": "RECORDING 3",
      "speaker": "",
      "text": "Reading is a fundamental skill that is essential for success in life.",
      "type": "narration",
      "words": 12,
      "start": 1610.583,
      "end": 1611.069,
      "matchedWords": 0
    },
    {
      "id": "line-122",
      "sectionId": "recording-3",
      "sectionTitle": "RECORDING 3",
      "speaker": "",
      "text": "It not only provides us with knowledge and information, but also helps us develop critical thinking, empathy, and imagination.",
      "type": "narration",
      "words": 19,
      "start": 1611.069,
      "end": 1611.84,
      "matchedWords": 0
    },
    {
      "id": "line-123",
      "sectionId": "recording-3",
      "sectionTitle": "RECORDING 3",
      "speaker": "",
      "text": "Reading exposes us to different ideas, cultures, and perspectives.",
      "type": "narration",
      "words": 9,
      "start": 1611.84,
      "end": 1612.205,
      "matchedWords": 0
    },
    {
      "id": "line-124",
      "sectionId": "recording-3",
      "sectionTitle": "RECORDING 3",
      "speaker": "",
      "text": "It allows us to learn about the experiences of people from all over the world and from different time periods.",
      "type": "narration",
      "words": 20,
      "start": 1612.205,
      "end": 1613.015,
      "matchedWords": 0
    },
    {
      "id": "line-125",
      "sectionId": "recording-3",
      "sectionTitle": "RECORDING 3",
      "speaker": "",
      "text": "This helps us develop empathy and understanding for others.",
      "type": "narration",
      "words": 9,
      "start": 1613.015,
      "end": 1613.38,
      "matchedWords": 0
    },
    {
      "id": "line-126",
      "sectionId": "recording-3",
      "sectionTitle": "RECORDING 3",
      "speaker": "",
      "text": "Reading also helps us develop critical thinking skills.",
      "type": "narration",
      "words": 8,
      "start": 1613.38,
      "end": 1613.705,
      "matchedWords": 0
    },
    {
      "id": "line-127",
      "sectionId": "recording-3",
      "sectionTitle": "RECORDING 3",
      "speaker": "",
      "text": "When we read, we have to analyze and evaluate the information we are presented with.",
      "type": "narration",
      "words": 15,
      "start": 1613.705,
      "end": 1614.313,
      "matchedWords": 0
    },
    {
      "id": "line-128",
      "sectionId": "recording-3",
      "sectionTitle": "RECORDING 3",
      "speaker": "",
      "text": "We have to distinguish between fact and opinion, and identify the author's purpose and point of view.",
      "type": "narration",
      "words": 17,
      "start": 1614.313,
      "end": 1615.002,
      "matchedWords": 0
    },
    {
      "id": "line-129",
      "sectionId": "recording-3",
      "sectionTitle": "RECORDING 3",
      "speaker": "",
      "text": "In addition, reading can improve our vocabulary, grammar, and writing skills.",
      "type": "narration",
      "words": 11,
      "start": 1615.002,
      "end": 1615.448,
      "matchedWords": 0
    },
    {
      "id": "line-130",
      "sectionId": "recording-3",
      "sectionTitle": "RECORDING 3",
      "speaker": "",
      "text": "It exposes us to different writing styles and helps us learn how to express ourselves more effectively.",
      "type": "narration",
      "words": 17,
      "start": 1615.448,
      "end": 1616.137,
      "matchedWords": 0
    },
    {
      "id": "line-131",
      "sectionId": "recording-3",
      "sectionTitle": "RECORDING 3",
      "speaker": "",
      "text": "Unfortunately, many people today do not read as much as they used to.",
      "type": "narration",
      "words": 13,
      "start": 1616.137,
      "end": 1616.664,
      "matchedWords": 0
    },
    {
      "id": "line-132",
      "sectionId": "recording-3",
      "sectionTitle": "RECORDING 3",
      "speaker": "",
      "text": "With the rise of social media and digital technology, people are spending more time watching videos and scrolling through social media feeds than reading books.",
      "type": "narration",
      "words": 25,
      "start": 1616.664,
      "end": 1617.678,
      "matchedWords": 0
    },
    {
      "id": "line-133",
      "sectionId": "recording-3",
      "sectionTitle": "RECORDING 3",
      "speaker": "",
      "text": "To encourage more people to read, we need to make reading more accessible and enjoyable.",
      "type": "narration",
      "words": 15,
      "start": 1617.678,
      "end": 1618.286,
      "matchedWords": 0
    },
    {
      "id": "line-134",
      "sectionId": "recording-3",
      "sectionTitle": "RECORDING 3",
      "speaker": "",
      "text": "This includes providing access to books in schools, libraries, and communities, and promoting reading as a fun and rewarding activity.",
      "type": "narration",
      "words": 20,
      "start": 1618.286,
      "end": 1619.097,
      "matchedWords": 0
    },
    {
      "id": "line-135",
      "sectionId": "recording-3",
      "sectionTitle": "RECORDING 3",
      "speaker": "Q22.",
      "text": "What are some of the benefits of reading?",
